    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nNeovim currently builds release artifacts for linux x86_64 and arm64, but not for riscv64. The RISC-V ecosystem is growing (SiFive boards, StarFive VisionFive 2, Milk-V, Sipeed LicheePi, etc.) and users on those platforms must build from source.\n\nThe main historical blocker was LuaJIT, which lacked official riscv64 support. This has been resolved: the [OpenResty LuaJIT fork](https://github.com/openresty/luajit2) includes riscv64 support, and Neovim already uses this fork.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nAdd `riscv64` to the Linux CI and release build matrix so that:\n1. PRs are validated against riscv64 builds (catching regressions early)\n2. Release tarballs and AppImages include a linux/riscv64 variant\n\nI have verified that Neovim builds and runs successfully on native riscv64 hardware using [RISE riscv64 runners](https://gitlab.com/riseproject/riscv64-ci-images) (GitHub-hosted runners with the `ubuntu-24.04-riscv` label, provided by the RISE Project): [successful CI run](https://github.com/gounthar/neovim/actions/runs/23350202292).\n\nA PR adding riscv64 to the release matrix will follow this issue.",
