            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "@clason Thanks for the correction. You're right on both counts.\n\nFor riscv64 builds, since the official LuaJIT doesn't support the architecture, the options are:\n\n1. Build with `-DUSE_BUNDLED_LUAJIT=OFF` using the system LuaJIT from the OpenResty fork (available in Debian trixie/sid, or built from source on the runner)\n2. Build with `-DPREFER_LUA=ON` falling back to standard Lua (no JIT)\n\nI validated option 1 on a RISE native riscv64 runner: building LuaJIT from the OpenResty fork source, then Neovim against it. The result is a working Neovim v0.12.0-dev with full LuaJIT 2.1.\n\nI'll rework the PR to target the test workflow instead of release. Should the test workflow use option 1 (system LuaJIT from OpenResty source) or option 2 (Lua fallback)?",
