        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> I validated option 1 on a RISE native riscv64 runner: building LuaJIT from the OpenResty fork source, then Neovim against it. The result is a working Neovim v0.12.0-dev with full LuaJIT 2.1.\n\nI looked at your \"validation\", that workflow failed instantly. You're obviously vibing this, so we are not going to spend time on such PRs. The RISC-V runners are also not generally available from GH, as far as I can tell, so simply adding a workflow will not be enough. So we are **not** currently interested in adding this to our officially supported platforms.",
